review_blob:
Poured from a bomber into a snifter light light golden yellow with minimial white head.
Aroma has a definite Belgian banana going on...
Flavor upfront was bitter?? Esters & really old dark banana. 
Seems way too watery to make a full mouth fill as I like my Belgian Golden Ales. A Leffe & La Chouffe wanna be. Like this brewery but they missed one BIG time.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter clear golden yellow with a off white head.
Aroma is malted peaches.
Flavor is upfront tropical fruits. Do not get much peaches but its not a loss. The sublte bitterness is a step away for STONE. Obviously the collaboratioin stressed less Stone signature flavor & more into the goodness of the Yakima & the greatness of 4 Hands (love 4H).
Balance is nice-noticed more peach as it warmed. Ahhhhhhh
beer_name: Stone / 4 Hands / Bale Breaker Sorry Not Sorry

review_blob:
Poured from a bottle purchased a few years back into a snifter the color of caramel with a thin white head.
Aroma says sticky sweetness. 
Flavor is flippin insanely sugared raisins slightly burnt. Carbonated. Feels smooth to the tongue. An excellent dessert brew paired with havarti. Going to savor this brew. Blessed to have another one stowed away to share with others down the road.

On tap at Toppling Goliath Brewery a cloudy light yellow orangw with a white head.
Aroma is tropical hops.
Flavor is exceptional JUICY!! Lots of orange going on here and smooth bittered hops. It is sweetly balanced for only 5.5% ABV. .

Poured on tap at Hoof Hearted Bottle (can) release cloudy more yellow than orange with a tremendous head.
Aroma is fruity juicy pine trees.
Flavor is sweet, getting peaches, mango(?) lots of bitter pine tree end. Dont get the 11.5% ABV at all.
This reminds me of a DIPA rather than a TIPA. There was a breadiness to the palate & it seemed diluted? Still a very good brew. Glad I went to bottle release and picked up a couple of 4 packs.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter brown black with a very minimal head.
Aroma chocolate dipped bell pepper.
Flavor is flat out awesome. Dark cocoa here with a touch of sweetness and ton of chili pepper at the finish. Like. WHOA!!! feel like I have a sore throat after comsuming. LOVE THIS STUFFF!!
Excellent blend of flavors. Grateful have a spare bomber to share at our next tasting.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter dark orange with a white head.
Aroma is citrus. Pineapple. Whiskey.
Flavor repeats the aroma, Sweet & juicy to the palate. Beautifully balanced. Outstanding barrel aged DIPA.

Poured from a bottle purchased at the brewery into a snifter dark opaque black brown with a dark tan head.
Aroma is CHOCOLATE!! Definite coffee. Sweetness.
Flavor is upfront dark cocoa. And a beautifully balanced coffee finish. A touch of vanilla. Do not get much bourbon. and the 10% ABV is completely hidden.O_o. An outstanding coffee porter like non other I have consumed. WOW>
beer_name: Heavy Seas Uncharted Waters: Blackbeards Breakfast

review_blob:
Pours from a 6-pk can into a tulip clear golden orange with a massive beige head.
Aroma is massive sugared pine trees.
Flavor is sweetly smooth up front and a barrel of bitterness at the finish. 
Higher ABV hides--and love it. Well above the usual DIPA. Thanks Revolution.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter glass darkest brown with a beige head that dissipated quickly.
Aroma is coconut, sweet caramel, cocoa.
Flavor reminds me of a Mounds candy bar with a chaser of rye whiskey. Totally beautiful blend to the palate. Wished I had picked up another bottle cuz this baby is gonna go down fast...screw savoring this baby!!

Poured from a growler rom a keg brought with Greg Koch for a meet & greet a rich dark amber with a huge off white head.
Aroma is burnt carmel pine trees.
Flavor is citrus with that biting classically Stone.

Poured from a bomber into a Revolution pint glass purchased at Revolution Brewing a goldenclear golden orange with a off white head.
Aroma is tropical pine trees.
Flavor is incredibly juicy. Earthy. Sweetly bitter. Mosaic is not over the top--makes for a phemon aroma!
One of the best brews from Revolution. This is one has it going on!

Poured from bottle into a snifter glass darkest of dark with a tan head.
Aroma is coffee sweetness with a touch of vanilla.
Flavort is blow your socks off marshmallow--really. and strong cocoa coffee.
Exquisite blend of flavors. Thick & chewy. Savaoring every sip is recommeneded.

Poured from a bombert into a snifter golden yellow with an off white head.
Aroma is totally gym BO!!!!! Lovin it.
Flavor is classic Stone. Bitterness in every sip. Quite dry in the finish-under sweet for a DIPA.
Overall a great anniversary brew.

Poured from a can into a snifter glass brown black with light beige head.
Aroma is brown sugared coffee.
Flavor is incredibly smooth cocoa coffee laced with vanilla. Sweet and almost a perfected balanced brew. LOVE this brew!!!!

Poured from a bomber purchased at Heavy Seas Brewery into a snifter golden with a beige head.
Aroma is Belgian. Banana & cloves-spicy.
Flavor is peppered spices. Fruity. Creamy. Finish is dry to the palate. Love the unique spiciness of this exceptional trippel.
beer_name: Heavy Seas Uncharted Waters: Plank III

review_blob:
Poured from a can into a pint glass a cloudy straw yellow with a white head.
Aroma is lemony high resin.
Flavor is crisp, bitingly bittiter finish. A worthy IPA.
beer_name: Hoof Hearted Musk Of The Minotaur

review_blob:
Poured a growler into a pint glass lightest orange yellow with a huge off white head.
Aroma is lemon, grass, juicy delicious blend to the palate. Bitter finish is right on target. As a huge Bodhi & Creeper fan this one is another top notch CBC brew.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter a darkest brown with effervescent jhead that quick left...
Aroma definitely has a cabernet scent. Malty. Such sweetness.
Flavor of thick boozy prunes. Berries. Molasses. Balanced quite well. Would have loved to nab a second bottle to lay down.

Poured from a bottle into a pint glass yellow gold with a beautiful off white pillow top head.
Aroma is lemon citrus pine trees.Im such a sucker for West Coast IPAs.Flavor is high hop but get the pils malt base. its subtle but there.
Not just an average brew IPA

Poured from bottle into a snifter darkest of brown black with a thin tan head.
Aroma is roasty funky sweet.
Flavor is subtle chocolalte malted. A thin feel to the palate for a stout. Its nice but I wont head out for another bottle...

Poured from a 4 pack of 12 oz bottles purchased in MD a dark amber with minimal head.
Aroma ber sweet hops.
Flavor is malty sweet with plenty of hops. Honey works here more than many other DIPA. A tasty brew
beer_name: Laughing Dog Sneaky Pete Imperial IPA

review_blob:
Bottle purchased on a brewery run thru Maryland and poured into a snifter reddish dark brown with minimal head.
Aroma is malty with dark fruits.
Flavor is mild for a dubbel. Quite Smooth.

Poured from bottle purchase in to a snifter pint glass deep yellow orange with plenty of head.
Aroma is hoppy grasses with subtle orange. Mild malts.
Flavor is full out pine trees, definite juicy oranges, a touch of maltiness.
Finish is not overly bitter. 10% ABV so not evident. Unless of course you drink this on an empty stomach after mowing the lawn....O_o.

Bomber purchased at Fyling Dog poured into a FD snifter.
Poured dark black brown cloudy. Thick with a tan head.
Aroma is cocoa raisins soaked in rum.
Taste duplicates the aroma almost perfectly. Some mild burnt malts. The burn tells me this isnt the usual porter. Love the bourbon barrel aged Gonzo of which several years have passed my lips. This one is worthy of slapping BA Gonzo in the face. O_o.

Poured from a bottle into my favorite Delirium tremens snifter the thickest most milky dark brown I have ever seen in a stout. Reminds me of muddy water but in a good way.
Aroma is roasted cocoa.
Flavor is oily like motor oil. Heavy dark chocolate bitter. Mild prunes.
To the palate bittersweet. Caramel. Incredible smoothness almost no carbonation. Delicious

Poured from a fresh bomberi into a Hoppin Frog pint glass cloudy lightest yellow orange with a thick white head.
Aroma is pine trees thick with orange.
Flavor is lovely citrus hoppy. Smooth resin. Grassy finish. And did I mention a delicious sweetness?
Another beautifully balanced brew from HF. Never dissappointed with this brewery. Ever.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Teeny Tiny Test Batch IPA Vol. 1

review_blob:
Poured from a pint can into a pint glass light yellow orange with a nice thick off white head.
Aroma is citrus bitterness hops.
Flavor is orange slight grapefruit. Pine trees. Earthy finish. Hidden 10.2%ABV is pretty freakin impressive.
Easily will buy another 4 pack.
beer_name: Hoof Hearted South of Eleven Imperial IPA

review_blob:
Poured from a bomber into a snifter darkest of dark with a tan head--looking like a planet through a telescope.
Aroma is RUM then cocoa dry. Slight vanilla.
Flavor is chocolate and slight rum. Caramelized barley roasted subtly.Bitter finish?
Smooth to the palate an unexpected beauty.
beer_name: Camerons Obsidian Imperial Porter Rum Barrel Aged

review_blob:
Poured from a bomber into a tall snifter darkest orange golden with a light beige head.
Aroma is pine trees (thinking Canadian Blue Spruce). Malts. Sugar.
Flavor is far better than anticipated. Pine tree resin with a beauitful sweetness. The bitter finish is very smooth to the palate. Flying Monkey is proving itself making some unique brews ie. Chocolate Manifesto & Acadian Groove Maple Porter--this one is a definite winner. Easily would purchase again.

Poured into a Spiegelau glass balck with a huge tan head.
Aroma is sweet bitterness some light roastiness.
Flavor is so beautifully DIPA with a coffee vanilla kick. 
Smooth and no over the top roastiness of some sub Black IPAs.
Thinking this is my fave of the planet series.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Uranus - The Magician

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob:
2014 bottle poured into a snifter mahogony brown with a beige head that quickly left.
Aroma is sweet boozy. That unique Belgian scent that makes me smile.
Flavor is thickly dark fruit spicy. Smooth. First had couple of years ago on tap at the The Lost Abbey. Seriously as delicious. A fave ever American made Belgian Quads.

poured from can into a pint glass golden yellow with a whitish head.
aroma is oranges bitter yet sweet.
flavor is bitter malty. slightness of rye to the palate. juicy orange off the map. blended well above the average.

Bottled poured into a snifter dark brown black with a thick brown head that left quickly.
Aroma is cocoa coffee sweetness
Flavor is impressive. Vanilla. Coffee. Bittersweet finish.
Nice blend of flavors yet carbonation felt a tad over the top. Maybe if I lay a bottle down for a few months it will settle into its prime. Dont get me wrong its a wonderful brew but its not as thick and chewy as I prefer in my BBRIS.
beer_name: MadTree Bourbon Barrel Aged Axis Mundi

review_blob:
Poured from a bottle into a snifter basic brown with a beige head that left quickly.
Aroma is boozy. Caramel. Sweet.
Flavor is cRaZy smooth. Definite whiskey but not over the top. Rich brown sugared toffee dipped in vanilla. Oak isnt in your face. Smooth like a babys butt. Incredible. Keep brewing Prairie. You got this.

First consumed on tap at 4 Hands brewery. Bought 4 bombers of which one of these poured into a pint glass a dark golden with a off white head.
Aromatic oranges in a pine forest comes to mind.
Flavor is superb. Caramel sweetness with juicy citrus. Nice bitter finish. Beautiful brew to the palate. Impressive!

Poured from a bottle purchased at 4 Hands into a pint glass lightest cloudy yellow with a white head.
Aroma is uber citrus lemon. Bitter notes. Know there is Brett here.
Flavor is socks off beautiful. Sassy sweet fruits with an impressive hops line up. Galaxy hops oh yeah.
Balanced exceptionally well. So flippin good!
beer_name: 4 Hands / Wicked Weed Super Flare IPA

review_blob:
Poured from a 12 oz bottle into a snifter glass dark golden with a slightly off white head.
Aroma is sweet like honey,clover, flowers with a touch of bitterness. Probably one of the most delectable brews I have inhaled in a long time. 
Flavorto the palate is flat out crazy beautiful. Sweet pine trees needles. Then definitely add in the freshly mowed lawn. Far better than most DIPAs. This brewery nailed the style almost perfectly. And it;s in Lawrence KS? Good thing my parents are KU grads or would have never believed something this good came from Kansas. LOVE!!!
beer_name: Free State Cloud Hopper Imperial IPA

review_blob:
Poured from a can into a snifter dark golden with a nice thick head.
Aroma is pine trees--oranges?
Flavor is juicy citrus with pine resin. Beautiful on the palate.

Poured from a bomber into a Surly Brewing Snifter from Darkness Day a cloudy amber with minimal head.
Aroma is WHISKEY then caramel sweetness. 
Flavor is sweet raisins caramel definite rye whiskey.
Smooth to the palate. Truly beautiful.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter--phenom bottle trade a golden yellow with a white head.
Aroma is juicy bitter oranges.
Flavor BLEW ME AWAY!!!! DIPA is my preferred style and had my fair share. This one is exceptional. Really worth the hype. 
Luscious to the palate and am blessed to have traded for 2 of these beauties.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter amber with an off white head.
Aroma is BOURBON>
Flavor is like sipping a ale drenched in a woody bourbon cask. Lots of timber & unique essence of booze. Flavors meld well. Possibly one of the most distinct brews I have consumed in a long time.
beer_name: Northgate Old Ale - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob:
Poured from a 4-17 bomber into a snifter glass cloudy orange yellow with a nice white head.
Aroma is pine trees grass & sweetness.
Flavor is spruce trees dipped in caramel. Finish is a balanced smoothness of bitterness. 
A juicy brew in all the right ways....

Poured from a bomber purchased at FFF into a 3F pint glass deep cloudy orange with a off white head.
Aroma is bitter citrus.
Flavor is juicy grapefruit, bitter pine, sweet booze. 
Another outstanding DIPA. Seriously they got this style down pat!!

Poured from a bomber into a snifter darkest brown black with a tan head that laced nicely.
Aroma is vanilla coconut subtle booze.
Flavor is better than aroma. Add cocoa and more bourbon. 
So smooth to the palate.Balanced. Beautiful.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter a dark brown with a beige head that quickly left.
Aroma of roasted hops. Slight hoppiness.
Flavor is sweet caramel. Dark cocoa. Lots of roasted malt.. Pine tree hops.
The balance is quite good and I am not a huge Clown Shoes fan. This is one of the more impressive brews.

Poured from a 2012 bomber into a Duvel snifter dark auburn brown with a light beige head.
Aroma is raisins with sweet Belgian caramelized sugar.
Flavor is one of my most favorite barley wines. Sweetly luscious dark fruit. Higher ABV almost non exsitant to the palate. Truly a spectacular brew.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter glass raspberry red with pretty much no head.
Aroma of a raspberry tart, 
Flavor is crisp. Sweet. Raspberry Jam & beautiful.
Smooth slight tartness. Balanced beautifully. Probably the best fruit brew. EVER. With the 9.2%...beautiful subtle.

Poured from a bomber into a snifter dark amber brown with a light beige head.
Aroma is flat out maple syrup when opened and I was 5-6 feet from the bottle.
Flavor is Aunt Jemina beautiful! Heavy maple and brown sugar. Booze but not crazy with the burn in the back of the throat. Slight bitterness in finish.
Love Flying Monkey special editions as they have never disappointed me. This one is sweet madness. Makes me want to head to IHOP and bring this bottle with me. Beautiful to the palate!!!
Kinda ticked I could only purchase one of these babies...would love to share another one with a group just to see their eyes pop. Good stuff!

Poured from a bottle into a pint glass dark clear amber red with a huge beige pillow top head.
Aroma is malted hops.
Flavor is crazy awesome. Pine trees, sweet malts-some pepper in the finish.
You got me at the pillow top head. LOVE!!
Then add the smoothness of this brew. Like so much went back and bought 2 more 4 packs. Must have again!!!!
beer_name: Fat Heads Bone Head Imperial Red Ale
